<h3>Surgical Procedures</h3>
<p>Waiting times for elective surgeries in the public system can be significant. According to data from the Ministerio de Sanidad, the average surgical waiting time in the Balearic Islands ranges from 90-180 days depending on the procedure. Some specific examples:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Cataract surgery:</strong> 80-150 days in public vs. 7-14 days in private</li>
  <li><strong>Hip or knee replacement:</strong> 120-240 days in public vs. 14-30 days in private</li>
  <li><strong>Hernia repair:</strong> 60-120 days in public vs. 7-21 days in private</li>
  <li><strong>Varicose vein surgery:</strong> 90-200 days in public vs. 14-30 days in private</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Important context:</strong> These waiting times apply to elective and non-urgent procedures. Urgent and life-threatening conditions (cancer, heart attacks, strokes, acute appendicitis, etc.) are treated promptly in both systems. The Spanish public system has specific time guarantees for cancer treatment, typically beginning within 15-30 days of diagnosis.</p>

<h3>Diagnostic Tests</h3>
<p>Waiting times for diagnostic imaging and tests also differ significantly:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>MRI scan:</strong> 30-90 days in public vs. 1-5 days in private</li>
  <li><strong>CT scan:</strong> 15-45 days in public vs. 1-3 days in private</li>
  <li><strong>Ultrasound:</strong> 15-30 days in public vs. same-day to 3 days in private</li>
  <li><strong>Blood tests:</strong> Same-day to 3 days in both systems</li>
  <li><strong>Endoscopy / Colonoscopy:</strong> 30-90 days in public vs. 3-10 days in private</li>
</ul>

<h2>Private Healthcare: How It Works</h2>

<h3>Overview and Main Advantages</h3>

<p>Private healthcare in Spain operates through insurance-based networks. When you purchase private health insurance, you gain access to the insurer''s network of doctors, specialists, clinics, and hospitals (<em>cuadro m&eacute;dico</em>). The key advantages of private healthcare include:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Dramatically shorter wait times:</strong> As shown in the data above, private specialists are typically available within days rather than weeks or months.</li>
  <li><strong>Direct specialist access:</strong> Many private insurers allow you to book directly with specialists without needing a GP referral first, saving time and an additional appointment.</li>
  <li><strong>Choice of doctor and hospital:</strong> You choose your preferred provider from within the insurer''s network, rather than being assigned based on your postcode.</li>
  <li><strong>Better facilities and comfort:</strong> Private hospitals typically offer single rooms, modern facilities, and a more hotel-like patient experience.</li>
  <li><strong>Language accessibility:</strong> Private clinics in Mallorca often have English-speaking (and German-speaking) doctors and administrative staff.</li>
  <li><strong>Extended consultation times:</strong> Private doctors typically spend 20-30 minutes per consultation vs. 5-10 minutes in the public system.</li>
  <li><strong>Modern digital tools:</strong> Telemedicine, online booking, digital prescriptions, health record apps, and 24/7 medical hotlines.</li>
</ul>

